text: National Harbor is a census-designated place along the Potomac River in Oxon Hill, Prince George's County, Maryland just south of Washington, D.C.. It began as a multi-use waterfront development. In the 2020 census, its population was 5,509. The conservative event CPAC is located in National Harbor. ==References== ==Other websites== *Baltimore Business Journal article Category:Census-designated places in Maryland
